    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>Security Architecture</title>
        <para>This data module describes the security architecture of the AQUA-OS operating 
        system, including quantum-ready cryptographic protections, secure boot, and runtime 
        security features compliant with DO-326A and ED-112A standards.</para>
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Security Objectives</title>
          <para>The security architecture addresses:</para>
          <para>- Protection against unauthorized access</para>
          <para>- Data integrity and confidentiality</para>
          <para>- Secure boot and attestation</para>
          <para>- Quantum-ready cryptographic algorithms</para>
          <para>- Runtime security monitoring</para>
        </levelledPara>
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Cryptographic Services</title>
          <para>The OS provides cryptographic services including:</para>
          <para>- Quantum-resistant key exchange (Kyber)</para>
          <para>- Digital signatures (Dilithium)</para>
          <para>- Symmetric encryption (AES-256)</para>
          <para>- Secure random number generation</para>
          <para>- Cryptographic key management</para>
        </levelledPara>
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Access Control</title>
          <para>Multi-level access control mechanisms:</para>
          <para>- Partition-level isolation enforced by MMU</para>
          <para>- Role-based access control for system services</para>
          <para>- Mandatory access control policies</para>
          <para>- Audit logging of security-relevant events</para>
        </levelledPara>
      </levelledPara>
    </description>
